
// The code demonstrates the use of [strings.builder] and [strings.builder.append] slots to construct a file path string dynamically. It appends various components like drive, folder, and file name to form a complete path. The [strings.builder.append] slot is used repeatedly to add each part of the path, allowing for dynamic string construction based on input arguments.
strings.builder
   strings.builder.append:x:@.arguments/*/drive
   strings.builder.append:":\\"
   strings.builder.append:x:@.arguments/*/folder
   strings.builder.append:"\\"
   strings.builder.append:x:@.arguments/*/file
